# What is a Loop?

A loop is a control statement that repeatedly executes a block of code as long as a specified condition is true.

---

# Why Do We Need Loops?

Loops help avoid writing the same code multiple times.

Instead of:

```java
System.out.println("Hello");
System.out.println("Hello");
System.out.println("Hello");
```

We can write:

```java
for(int i = 1; i <= 3; i++){
    System.out.println("Hello");
}
```

---

