# Common Mistakes

❌ Wrong condition

```java
for(int i = 1; i >= 5; i++)
```

Loop never executes.

---

❌ Missing update

```java
for(int i = 1; i <= 5;)
```

May create an infinite loop.

---

❌ Wrong update direction

```java
for(int i = 10; i >= 1; i++)
```

Infinite loop.

---

# Revision Box

✅ Loop → Repeats a block of code.

✅ Initialization → Runs once.

✅ Condition → Checked before every iteration.

✅ Update → Runs after each iteration.

✅ Infinite Loop → Never ends.

✅ O(n) → Depends on input size.

✅ O(1) → Fixed number of iterations.

